For 820 nm degenerate pump-probe measurements in Fig. 3(a and b), it might be straightforward but incorrect to attribute the ECA to the transition from the Mn IB states to the bandtail states. Because the ECA from the Mn IB states and the band-filling effects both reflect the carrier lifetime in the Mn IB, they should be modeled with the same exponential functions. In other words, they are not distinguishable in only one Aiexp(−t/τi)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
