				\begin{document}$${A}_{i}\exp (-t/{\tau }_{i})$$\end{document}. For 820 nm degenerate pump-probe measurements in Figs 3(a) and 4, the lifetimes of carriers in the Mn IB states were dominated by the band-filling effects because under our experimental conditions, only 10–16 cm−3 carriers at most were generated in the Mn-IB states of Mn-GaN. Transition of the probe pulse from the valence band to the Mn-IB should overwhelm the effects of ECA from the Mn-IB states.

